00:00:00.680 --> 00:00:04.730
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, DC.

00:00:07.260 --> 00:00:11.730
&gt;&gt; BARD Express: Searching
the BARD Collection.

00:00:12.930 --> 00:00:18.730
&gt;&gt; Judy: Hello, I'm Judy Dixon,
Consumer Relations Officer at NLS.

00:00:18.730 --> 00:00:21.850
In this edition of the
BARD Express How-To Series,

00:00:21.850 --> 00:00:26.420
I'm going to cover searching
the BARD collection for titles.

00:00:26.420 --> 00:00:31.180
To search the collection, from
the BARD Express Main Menu select

00:00:31.180 --> 00:00:32.970
search BARD.

00:00:32.970 --> 00:00:38.940
You will be presented with a
keyword search term edit box.

00:00:38.940 --> 00:00:44.100
You can enter a keyword or you can
tab over to the Search by Type drop

00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:48.380
down box and change the
search type to search

00:00:48.380 --> 00:00:52.570
by DB number, author, or title.

00:00:52.570 --> 00:00:58.220
You can also narrow your results by
using the Subject Filter to exclude

00:00:58.220 --> 00:01:01.510
or include various subjects.

00:01:01.510 --> 00:01:05.330
By default, all subjects
are included.

00:01:05.330 --> 00:01:07.790
Enter a key word in the box.

00:01:07.790 --> 00:01:12.470
For this example I am going
to use the word Winter.

00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:15.670
Press enter to initiate the search.

00:01:15.670 --> 00:01:17.410
&gt;&gt; NVDA: Winter.

00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:20.490
Loaded search BARD
winter items 1 to 50.

00:01:20.490 --> 00:01:22.060
Search BARD.

00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:26.190 position:56%
Search BARD, press F1 for help list.

00:01:26.190 --> 00:01:27.810
A prairie boy's winter.

00:01:27.810 --> 00:01:32.080
Author Kurelek, William, 1 of 50.

00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:35.010
&gt;&gt; Judy: The available books
containing this word will be

00:01:35.010 --> 00:01:37.440
presented in a list view.

00:01:37.440 --> 00:01:40.870
The focus will be on the
first book in the list.

00:01:40.870 --> 00:01:45.300
Use the arrow up and down keys
to browse the search results.

00:01:45.300 --> 00:01:48.880
From this screen you can add
titles to your wish list,

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:52.570
download them, or access
their details.

00:01:52.570 --> 00:01:57.260
Additionally, you may change
the sort order of the book list.

00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:00.960
If you are going to download
or add to your wish list more

00:02:00.960 --> 00:02:06.450 position:56%
than one title from the list, I
recommend you use the advanced view.

00:02:06.450 --> 00:02:12.040
Switch to the advanced view using
the keyboard shortcut control L.

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:15.280
For more information on
transferring and downloading books

00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:21.520
and managing your wish list see
the other tutorials in this series.

00:02:21.520 --> 00:02:25.390
&gt;&gt; This has been a presentation
of the Library of Congress.

